San Antonio police officers issued a fine to local chef and activist Joan Cheever for feeding the homeless at Maverick Park April 7 . 
 Cheever founded The Chow Train non-profit food truck in 2005 to feed the city's poor . 
 Has a commercially licensed mobile food truck where she prepares her meals, but she serves them out of her personal pickup truck . 
 Cheever accused city officials of violating her freedom of religion because she considers cooking and feeding the poor a free exercise of her faith . 
 